### CSS Box Shadow

**box-shadow** adds shadow effects around an element.

---

### Syntax

```css
box-shadow: offset-x offset-y blur spread color inset;
```

| Value | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| `offset-x` | Yes | Horizontal shift (+ = right) |
| `offset-y` | Yes | Vertical shift (+ = down) |
| `blur` | No | Blur radius (default 0) |
| `spread` | No | Shadow size expansion |
| `color` | No | Shadow color (default = text) |
| `inset` | No | Inner shadow instead of outer |

---

### Basic Examples

```css
/* Simple drop shadow */
box-shadow: 2px 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);

/* No offset, soft shadow */
box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);

/* Spread */
box-shadow: 0 0 0 5px blue; /* Like a border */

/* Inset (inner shadow) */
box-shadow: inset 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
```

---

### Multiple Shadows

```css
box-shadow:
  0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1),
  0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
```

---

### Common Shadow Patterns

```css
/* Card shadow (subtle) */
.card {
  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

/* Elevated card */
.card-elevated {
  box-shadow: 0 10px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
}

/* Button shadow */
.btn {
  box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}
.btn:hover {
  box-shadow: 0 6px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
}

/* Inset for pressed effect */
.btn:active {
  box-shadow: inset 0 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}

/* Outline/border effect */
.focus-ring:focus {
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(66, 153, 225, 0.5);
}
```

---

### Box Shadow vs Filter: Drop Shadow

```css
/* Box shadow - follows box shape */
box-shadow: 5px 5px 10px black;

/* Filter drop shadow - follows element outline (including transparency) */
filter: drop-shadow(5px 5px 10px black);
```

`drop-shadow()` respects `border-radius` and clipped content; `box-shadow` always follows the box model.

> **Best Practice:** Use multiple subtle shadows layered together for realistic depth.
